						<div class="postbody">What I mean about &quot;special chips&quot; are non custom chips made by Nintendo.  <br /><br />I am all for pics!  I recently learned about assembling the cic hex into a pic.  So if there was a pic alternative for the Mad1, I'm all for that.<br /><br />The 64k SRAMs are widely used I the 1A3M, 1J3M 2A3M, BJ3M, 2A3B, and other variants carts.  The &quot;3&quot; being the 64k designations.<br /><br />The super fx carts use 256k and 512 k SRAMs.<br /><br />Edit:  I am aware (and own) several of the repo carts including the SD2snes, ever drive, powerpak, and 1 other.     My goal is to learn how any why they work.  Building one of my own is more for learning and to see how it's done.  <br /><br />I have made all kinds of adapter for cartridges (see my YouTube) but I have never made a cart.  The Mad1 is really the one area that I don't know how to get around.<br /><br />Mark</div>

